1
00:00:03,389 --> 00:00:06,629
There’re many different ways 
that people can measure wealth.

2
00:00:09,464 --> 00:00:13,598
How does the original
Supreme Personality of Godhead,

3
00:00:13,598 --> 00:00:16,228
the Supreme Reality,
measure value?

4
00:00:16,598 --> 00:00:19,948
[Devotion is Measured in the Inverse]

5
00:00:20,980 --> 00:00:24,878
So, if He gets the breeze
from the garment of Rādhārāṇī

6
00:00:24,878 --> 00:00:27,878
upon Him, 
His divine form,

7
00:00:27,878 --> 00:00:32,758
He considers that to be 
the most valuable treasure.

8
00:00:33,372 --> 00:00:34,568
That Kṛṣṇa, who

9
00:00:34,568 --> 00:00:40,498
yogīndra-durgama-gatir madhusūdano ’pi
tasyā namo ’stu vṛṣabhānu-bhuvo diśe ’pi
[Rādhā-rasa-sudha-nidhi: 2]

10
00:00:40,498 --> 00:00:43,166
well, that’s Mahāprabhu, 
same theme with

11
00:00:43,166 --> 00:00:46,406
sureśānāṁ durgaṁ gatir atiśayenopaniṣadāṁ
[Cc: 2.4.51]

12
00:00:46,406 --> 00:00:50,848
Who … the great yogis, 
theу’re trying to get a glimpse of,

13
00:00:50,848 --> 00:00:56,120
the Upanishads, the Gods …

14
00:00:59,112 --> 00:01:03,926
When Kṛṣṇa as the baby and Trinаvarta, 
He went in the sky,

15
00:01:03,926 --> 00:01:05,000
part of the pastime,

16
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,064
they say, one of the reasons 
He went in the sky

17
00:01:07,064 --> 00:01:11,013
is to let the Goddesses, Gods 
and Goddesses like, have a look.

18
00:01:11,013 --> 00:01:13,782
[Laughing]

19
00:01:14,122 --> 00:01:19,442
So, who’s durgaṁ—very difficult 
to have a glimpse of …

20
00:01:19,636 --> 00:01:24,372
Brahmā is trying to get 
an audience with Kṛṣṇa.

21
00:01:24,372 --> 00:01:27,752
muhyanti yat sūrayaḥ 
[SB: 1.1.1]

22
00:01:33,423 --> 00:01:36,979
That Kṛṣṇa considers 
Himself so fortunate

23
00:01:36,979 --> 00:01:42,555
to be blessed by the breeze from 
the garment of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.

24
00:01:42,555 --> 00:01:50,699
So, the conclusion of Prabodhānanda Saraswatī Ṭhākur 
is a special note.

25
00:01:50,699 --> 00:01:57,841
He says, “Therefore, She is so great, 
She is so exalted,

26
00:01:57,841 --> 00:02:05,491
so extraordinary, so exceptional,
that I consider the direction

27
00:02:05,491 --> 00:02:11,141
in which She appeared 
to be worshipable.”

28
00:02:12,244 --> 00:02:18,344
Well, those in a … Her …
the sādhakas, in the lowest position,

29
00:02:18,344 --> 00:02:24,043
they are voyeuristically 
envisioning themselves

30
00:02:24,061 --> 00:02:29,647
as servitors in the Divine domain, 
in the upper world,

31
00:02:29,647 --> 00:02:35,227
in the most confidential region
of the spiritual existence.

32
00:02:35,227 --> 00:02:38,725
They have …
those, who are newly recruited

33
00:02:38,725 --> 00:02:40,765
and acquainted 
with Kṛṣṇa consciousness

34
00:02:40,765 --> 00:02:46,045
projecting themselves 
into those situations.

35
00:02:47,093 --> 00:02:52,781
Someone who is actually there: 
ashta-sakhi Tuṅga-vidyā—

36
00:02:52,781 --> 00:02:56,188
Prabodhānanda Saraswatī 
in Gaura-līla—says,

37
00:02:56,188 --> 00:03:00,449
“The direction in which She appeared 
is worshipable to me!

38
00:03:00,449 --> 00:03:03,627
That’s close enough for me.”

39
00:03:03,627 --> 00:03:06,292
That’s what’s said by someone, 
who’s actually there

40
00:03:06,292 --> 00:03:08,789
and eyewitnessed to all 
of these things.

41
00:03:09,199 --> 00:03:12,707
And eyewitnessed to how Kṛṣṇa feels 
when He’s blessed

42
00:03:12,707 --> 00:03:16,305
with the breeze of the garment 
of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.

43
00:03:16,305 --> 00:03:21,954
He says, “The direction in which 
She appears is worshipable to me.”

44
00:03:22,174 --> 00:03:26,447
So, the system 
for measuring devotional magnitude

45
00:03:26,447 --> 00:03:28,847
is always in the inverse.

